.SH "NAME"
Bio::Tools::Run::Analysis::soap \- A SOAP\-based access to the analysis tools
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
Do not use this object directly, it is recommended to access it and use
it through the \f(CW\*(C`Bio::Tools::Run::Analysis\*(C'\fR module:
.PP
.Vb 3
\&  use Bio::Tools::Run::Analysis;
\&  my $tool = Bio::Tools::Run::Analysis\->new(\-access => \*(Aqsoap\*(Aq,
\&                                            \-name   => \*(Aqseqret\*(Aq);
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This object allows to execute and to control a remote analysis tool
(an application, a program) using the \s-1SOAP\s0 middleware,
.PP
All its public methods are documented in the interface module
\&\f(CW\*(C`Bio::AnalysisI\*(C'\fR and explained in tutorial available in the
\&\f(CW\*(C`analysis.pl\*(C'\fR script.
